Ex 2

library(MASS)
set.seed(34)

N <- 40
sigma_e <- 1
sigma_x <- 1
x <- rnorm(N, 0, sigma_x)
epsilon <- rnorm(N, 0, sigma_e)
y <- x + x^2 + epsilon

model <- lm(y~ x + I(x^2))
y_pred <- predict(model, newdata=data.frame(x=x))

# Empirical test error
empirical_test_error <- mean((y_pred- y)^2)
print(paste("Empirical Test Error:", empirical_test_error))
## [1] "Empirical Test Error: 1.15097460486958"
# Analytical estimate of test error
bias_squared <- 0 # OLS standard assumptions
variance <- var(model$residuals)
analytical_test_error <- bias_squared + variance + sigma_e^2
print(paste("Analytical Test Error (approximated):", analytical_test_error))
## [1] "Analytical Test Error (approximated): 2.18048677422521"

aic_val <- sapply(models, AIC)

(d)

new_data <- lapply(101:200, function(i) {
  set.seed(i)
  y <- x - 2 * x ^ 2 + rnorm(100)
})

#negative likelihood function
nll <- function(model, y) {
  fitted_model <- lm(formula = model, data = data.frame(y = y, x = x))
  - 2 * logLik(fitted_model)
}

ll_data <- lapply(models, function(model_x) {
  sapply(new_data, nll, model = model_x)
})

in_sample_err <- sapply(ll_data, mean)


models_resutls <- data.frame(AIC = aic_val, In_err = in_sample_err)

library(dplyr)

(a)

set.seed(1)
x <- rnorm(100)
y <- x - 2 * x ^ 2 + rnorm(100)

data = data.frame(x = x, y = y)

models <- list(
  model1 = lm(y ~ x, data = data),
  model2 = lm(y ~ x + I(x ^ 2), data = data),
  model3 = lm(y ~ x + I(x ^ 2) + I(x ^ 3), data = data),
  model4 = lm(y ~ x + I(x ^ 2) + I(x ^ 3) + I(x ^ 4), data = data)
)

(b+c) Leave-One-Out Cross-Validation

loocv <- function(model) {
  SE <- vector()
  
  for (i in seq_along(y)) {
    train <- data[-i, ]
    test <- data[i, ]
    
    lm.fit <- lm(model, data = train)
    lm.pred <- predict(lm.fit, newdata = test)
    
    SE.i <- (lm.pred - test$y) ^ 2
    SE <- rbind(SE, SE.i)
  }
  MSE.LOOCV <- mean(SE)
  return(MSE.LOOCV)
}

(b+c) Leave-One-Out Cross-Validation

kfold <- function(model, k = 5) {
  MSE.k <- vector()
  
  for (i in 1:k) {
    fold <- data %>%
      mutate(row_id = row_number(), section = ntile(row_number(), k)) |>
      group_by(section) |>
      filter(section == i) |>
      pull(row_id)
    
    train <- data[-fold, ]
    test <- data[fold, ]
    
    lm.fit <- lm(model, data = train)
    lm.pred <- predict(lm.fit, newdata = test)
    
    SE.fold <- (lm.pred - test$y) ^ 2
    MSE.fold <- mean(SE.fold)
    MSE.k <- rbind(MSE.k, MSE.fold)
  }
  MSE.kfold <- mean(MSE.k)
  MSE.kfold
}

Results

rand_seed <- ceiling(abs(rnorm(2) * 200))

results <- function(seed) {
  set.seed(rand_seed[1])
  loocv_b <- sapply(models, loocv)
  kfold_b <- sapply(models, kfold)
  return(data.frame(
    LOOCV = loocv_b,
    KFCV = kfold_b,
    seed = seed
  ))
}

for (i in 1:2) {
  print(knitr::kable(results(rand_seed[i]), format = "simple"))
}

Ex 8

library(MASS)
library(glmnet)

Data generation

draw_data <- function(trial) {
  #setup
  set.seed(trial)
  d <- 100
  n <- 1000
  
  mean_vector <- rep(0, d)
  cov_matrix <- diag(d)
  eps <- rnorm(n, mean = 0, sd = sqrt(0.1))
  
  x <- mvrnorm(n, mu = mean_vector, Sigma = cov_matrix)
  y <- matrix(rowSums(x[, 1:10]) + eps, ncol = 1)
  
  train_index <- 1:100
  train_x <- x[train_index, ]
  train_y <- y[train_index, ]
  test_x <- x[-train_index, ]
  test_y <- y[-train_index, ]
  
  fit <- glmnet(train_x, train_y, alpha = 1, standardize = TRUE)
  prediction <- predict(fit, newx = test_x, s = fit$lambda)
  
  mse_fn <- function(predicted) mean((test_y - predicted) ^ 2)
  
  mse <- apply(prediction, 2, mse_fn)
  best_lambda_index <- which.min(mse)
  best_lambda <- fit$lambda[best_lambda_index]
  
  coeffs <- coef(fit, s = best_lambda)
  
  true_positive <- sum(coeffs[1:10 + 1] != 0)
  false_positive <- sum(coeffs[11:100 + 1] != 0)
  
  tpr = true_positive /length(1:10 + 1)
  fpr = false_positive /length(11:100 + 1)
  
  results = c(true_pos_rate =tpr, fasle_pos_rate= fpr, best_lambda = best_lambda)
  return(results)
}
results <- data.frame(do.call(rbind, lapply(300:400, draw_data)))
plot(results[,1], ylab = "True positive rate")

secret_message <- paste0("On average ",round(mean(results[,2]), digits = 3), "% of variables are falsely included in the model (as if they were relevant).")
print(secret_message)
## [1] "On average 0.249% of variables are falsely included in the model (as if they were relevant)."
hist(results[,2],main = "Distribution of FPR", xlab = "False positive rate")

hist(results[,3],main = "Distribution of optimal lambdas", xlab = expression(lambda))

library(ISLR)
library(dplyr)
library(MASS)

data("Wage", package = "ISLR")
Wage <- Wage %>%
  select(-logwage, -region)
Wage$year <- Wage$year - 2000

get_mode <- function(x) {
  unique_x <- unique(x)
  unique_x[which.max(tabulate(match(x, unique_x)))]
}
categorical_vars <- sapply(Wage, is.factor)
categorical_vars["education"] <- FALSE
categorical_vars
##       year        age     maritl       race  education   jobclass     health 
##      FALSE      FALSE       TRUE       TRUE      FALSE       TRUE       TRUE 
## health_ins       wage 
##       TRUE      FALSE
modes <- sapply(Wage[categorical_vars], get_mode)
modes
##         maritl           race       jobclass         health     health_ins 
##     2. Married       1. White  1. Industrial 2. >=Very Good         1. Yes 
## 15 Levels: 1. Never Married 2. Married 3. Widowed 4. Divorced ... 2. No
Wage$maritl <- relevel(Wage$maritl, ref = "2. Married")
Wage$race <- relevel(Wage$race, ref = "1. White")
Wage$jobclass <- relevel(Wage$jobclass, ref = "1. Industrial")
Wage$health_ins <- relevel(Wage$health_ins, ref = "1. Yes")


last_year <- max(Wage$year)

train_data <- Wage %>% filter(year < last_year)
test_data <- Wage %>% filter(year == last_year)


dim(train_data)
## [1] 2611    9
dim(test_data)
## [1] 389   9
# Contrasts for 'education'
contrasts(train_data$education) <- contr.sdif(levels(train_data$education))

# Orthogonal polynomials of order 4 for 'age'
train_data$age_poly <- poly(train_data$age, degree = 4)
test_data$age_poly <- poly(test_data$age, degree = 4, coefs = attr(train_data$age_poly, "coefs"))

# Create model matrices for training and testing
train_matrix <- model.matrix(~ age_poly + education + ., data = train_data)
test_matrix <- model.matrix(~ age_poly + education + ., data = test_data)


y_train <- train_data$wage

# ridge regression (alpha = 0) / lasso regression (alpha = 1)
set.seed(1634)
ridge_model <- cv.glmnet(train_matrix, y_train, alpha = 0, lambda = 10^seq(4, -2, length = 100), standardize = TRUE, intercept = TRUE)
lasso_model <- cv.glmnet(train_matrix, y_train, alpha = 1, lambda = 10^seq(4, -2, length = 100), standardize = TRUE, intercept = TRUE)

plot(ridge_model)

plot(lasso_model)

ridge_coeff_1se <- coef(ridge_model, s = "lambda.1se")
lasso_coeff_1se <- coef(lasso_model, s = "lambda.1se")



# Define the response variable for testing
y_test <- test_data$wage

# Make predictions using lambda.min and lambda.1se for both models
ridge_pred_min <- predict(ridge_model, newx = test_matrix, s = "lambda.min")
ridge_pred_1se <- predict(ridge_model, newx = test_matrix, s = "lambda.1se")

lasso_pred_min <- predict(lasso_model, newx = test_matrix, s = "lambda.min")
lasso_pred_1se <- predict(lasso_model, newx = test_matrix, s = "lambda.1se")

# Calculate the MSE
mse_ridge_min <- mean((y_test - ridge_pred_min)^2)
mse_ridge_1se <- mean((y_test - ridge_pred_1se)^2)
mse_lasso_min <- mean((y_test - lasso_pred_min)^2)
mse_lasso_1se <- mean((y_test - lasso_pred_1se)^2)

# Print the MSE values
cat("MSE for Ridge (lambda.min):", mse_ridge_min, "\n")
## MSE for Ridge (lambda.min): 0.0002007065
cat("MSE for Ridge (lambda.1se):", mse_ridge_1se, "\n")
## MSE for Ridge (lambda.1se): 0.0002007065
cat("MSE for Lasso (lambda.min):", mse_lasso_min, "\n")
## MSE for Lasso (lambda.min): 0.0001059782
cat("MSE for Lasso (lambda.1se):", mse_lasso_1se, "\n")
## MSE for Lasso (lambda.1se): 0.0001059782

accuracy <- function(m) {
  TN <- m[1, 1]  # True Negatives
  TP <- m[2, 2]  # True Positives
  return((TP + TN) / sum(m))
}

lapply(list(conf_matrix_min, conf_matrix_1se), accuracy)
